name: Sanur Harbour
address: 87J6+887, Jl. Matahari Terbit, Sanur Kaja, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali, Indonesia
review 1:
Probably the best harbour I've been to so far during my trip in Bali and Lombok. The staff are great, check-in processes are prompt and professional and there is an air conditioned waiting area with a great view and with some limited charging points

In some ways this terminal resembles an airport with announcements for boat departures and a couple of gates where passengers go through to head down to their boats. The boats are also docked on a proper pier
review 2: Huge space, clean and beautiful harbor, but unfortunately the toilet didn‚Äôt function well. There are a lot of coffee shops and restaurants so you can have breakfast here. You can go to Nusa Penida island by boat from here, it takes around 40 minutes.
review 3:
Very busy, allot of traffic to drive or ride down, plan accordingly.
Get to gate and wait 30 to 45 mins for the boat, come in early. Try buying online or else you will have to talk to someone and my rip you in the process.
Inside the waiting area very clean, spacious & cool. long walks.
review 4:
Pretty good harbour infrastructure, just please add waiting seats at the front. It'll be very helpful because passengers are standing randomly at the front, flocking with travel groups and the boatline. And build a toilet accessible for people who are not boarding or arriving.
Please also put information board of which boat is departing to where on what time at the front, so it will be helpful. What is the point of having a building if it only serves as a gate before departing to the boat
review 5: The new sanur harbour just really good. Good ticketing, no more wait too long, and very orderly than before. And the speed boat on time with the schedule. And we don't need to get wet when we want to get on a boat now!

name: Sunrise Beach
address: Sanur Kaja, Denpasar Selatan, Denpasar City, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1:
A nice local hangout, great place for sunrise with plenty of spaces to sit. On the rock by the sea, the ledge, proper seating areas (plenty).

It's located next to Pelabuhan Sanur which also means it can get uncomfortably crowded. I usually avoid it during weekends because those were the day when teenagers like to hang out and some shops cater to them by playing loud music. It would be difficult to get parking as well because it's full, unless you come early in the morning. I mean early! Before 6.30 or earlier!

Good:
- magnificent sunrise, therefore its name
- they have tidied up the motorcycle parking area, now it's more spacious and clean
- plenty of seat and place for you to watch the sunrise while contemplating life
- food: a lot of local food with very good local price
- pet friend;y
- plenty of parking (watch out for timing)

Not so good:
- sometimes there are many teenager that prompt the shop to play noisy music
- parking can be tedious if you come here other than early in the morning. Was stuck in parking lot for more than one hour before, unable to get out. It should be better now since they opened alternate parking space. Haven't tried, wouldn't want to try it myself.
- You can park at Bangsal beach and walk here, it's very near and there are usually some parking space there even though you arrive later.

They raise the parking price now. It used to be 5k and 2k for car and motorcycle for the first 3 hours, now they charge hourly at 2k/hour for car. It's still okay, and understandable, however they put the price change only when you are on the exit gate (not entry). Motorcycle can access from Bangsal beach through gang pacar.
review 2: Sunrise Beach at sunrise. Was peaceful walking along here and watching the day begin. Gets busy after 6.30AM with all the early birds here to enjoy the view and the freshness of the morning
review 3:
Having a good track for jogging and enjoying the view from wonderful Sanur Beach.

A lot of people visit this place in the weekend and I'm surprised at first time come here I see the full of motorbike in the parking area. But actually this place is really something. U can jogging, walking, bycling, yoga, etc.

Of course there are many food stand, so u can buy some food and drink.

This is an incredible and enjoyable place
review 4: Not quite lucky this time.. the cloud is in the horizon. But the place is nice. Parking is abundant in the morning. Since its a ferry port to nusa penida it will get very crowded in the afternoon and high seasson. Come early and go home early to catch the sun
review 5:
Even though this place called Sunrise Beach, spending time here at noon still recommended to have a quality time, or enjoying the sound-wave, or walking, cycling or people watching, or all at once.
Easy to access, many food stall and coffeeshop. I haven‚Äôt try all coffee here, so couldn‚Äôt really recommend one for you. Anyway, you still can get lumpia here (actually everywhere), please follow your gut feeling to choose for your tummy and yummy.
Not crowded preferably? Come here during weekday. Yap, so hot ü•µü•µ‚òÑÔ∏è‚òÑÔ∏è don‚Äôt forget put the sunacreen, shade and cover or cap.
Not too busy and crowded here (compare to other beach around Denpasar).

name: Sanur Agung Hotel
address: Jl. Bypass Ngurah Rai No.174, Sanur, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: This was the first hotel/cottage we booked for our Bali trip. Was a 40-minute drive to the hotel. Check-in was seamless as we pre-booked on Agoda. They confirmed our booking and assigned us room 104 located on the main floor. The room had one double bed and one single bed, a small fridge, a tv, a table, etc. It was equipped with AC but no fan. The room had bottled water and toiletries. The room wasn't big but did the job. The only thing we did not anticipate was that the washroom had see-through glass and not wall. The staff were super friendly, and they cleaned/restocked the room regularly. The swimming pool was maintained daily. A few downsides we experienced include a leak in the washroom, no dedicated space to dry our clothes, and their restaurant only offered breakfast till 10 am and only tea/coffee afterward. They did, however, have cup noodles and other beverages available for purchase. We were able to get a hairdryer and electric kettle from the reception. The hotel is adjacent to a very busy highway, which was good for us as we rented a car to drive ourselves and included ample parking. Additionally, the hotel was super close to many restaurants, warung, gas stations, and convenient stores. It was walking distance from Sanur Harbor, which was super convenient for us. One thing we loved was that the whole hotel was filled with plants. We also met a friendly cat, we named him/her meow. Please feed him if possible. Overall, we had a pleasant stay and definitely recommend them.
review 2:
You get what u pay for -  It is a budget hotel.
We are simply staying for 1 night because it is close to the harbor. Maybe more suitable for students & back packers ect.

‚óè Cons
‚Ä¢ Rooms are tiny with strange colour scheme & weird dirty brown wooly blanket.
‚Ä¢ Cramped for 2 people & suitcases.
‚Ä¢ Dirty scummy,  gross bathroom. Needs a decent scrub down for sure with some proper chemicals. Some weird contraption on the shower head as well.
‚Ä¢ Spiderwebs in the rooms.

‚óè Positives
‚ñ™Ô∏é Budget friendly
‚Ä¢ WiFi works
‚Ä¢ Lots of restaurants walking distance.
‚ñ™Ô∏é Pool ( kind of clean)
‚ñ™Ô∏é Close to the harbor
‚Ä¢ Service was average.
review 3: Worst hotel iv ever stayed in bali. Booked and paid for ‚Äòdeluxe‚Äô room. Got our room that is a triple standard went to reception to advise and she said ‚Äòyeah we have no deluxe rooms available‚Äô so i paid for a product i have not got. Rooms are really dirty and smell musty/damp. Very small rooms look nothing like the photos! Hotel is located right on a busy road, balcony is a shared balcony so no privacy. Tv does not work at all, pillows and bedding smells musty and dirty (slept in my clothes) AC poor also cleaners knocked us up at 9am after already having a rubbish sleep due to being to hot. Bathroom/toilet area smells awful of pee and needs some bleach to clean inside the toilet and change the mouldy shower curtain. Stayed in much nicer hotels for much cheaper than here
review 4: It's the worst place ever! I woke up in the morning to find a staff peeping into the my room through the window! I called him out immediately and went and complained to the front office about it. They did ABSOLUTELY NOTHING ABOUT IT. They asked me which room and were super casual about it like they hardly even cared. I went back to the room to find him cleaning the room next to mine like NOTHING EVER HAPPENED. It was super scary and traumatic and to see they hardly even cared. I checked out soon and left the place to NEVER EVER go back there. Stay safe and don't go there ever!
review 5: Power was out for hours today, everyone complains but the staff just relax on their phone. The pool is disgusting, and rooms are very dirty. I feel like the 5 stars on this are bots. Stay away from this place. Plenty of cheap hotels around with better service and cleaning up to good standards

name: Warung Be Sanur - Pantai Mataharai Terbit Sanur
address: Jl. Matahari Terbit No.1, Sanur Kaja, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1: they have this fried fish, rice and fish soup for 44000k reasonable price and tasty sambal
review 2:
Open early, i was there at 8am on a sunday morning and I can already ordered the fish package. Great for heavy breakfast craving.

This place has fried fish roe unlike the other branches, i love the texture.

The place is non air con, but still ok.
review 3: They offer a very similar fish combo meal like that in Mak Beng, but they also serve other local dishes. Came here since our driver recommended this. I personally prefer Mak Beng'a version more. Found the chilli here is on the sweeter side instead of savoury. Found the fried fish is a tad dry- probably because of the type of the fish. Soup is delicious though, and it came with generous amount of fish too. If you don't wanna queue at Mak Beng, this is a great alternative!
review 4:
140k for Fish soup with Rice (not the set), Mee Goreng (fried noodles), a vanilla milkshake and a strawberry smoothie. I think it's worth it! Nice breakfast while waiting for our ferry.

Note that the fish in the fish soup is really bony tho.. I got lazy to eat it. I would try the fish head instead if I end up here again. The soup is spicy, salty
review 5: Be Sanur fish soup is an old school culinary dish. The menu at the Be Sanur stall is fried fish and chili sauce, plus white rice. A soup with ‚ÄúBase Genep‚Äù spices typical of Bali, the delicacy seems to stick to the tongue. The texture of the meat is dense and not easily crushed. Even though it is made from fish, it does not have the slightest fishy taste. Savory, spicy, sweet and a little sour in one. The sambal served is dark in color because of the shrimp paste mixture. Fried fish that has been smeared with chili sauce, then slurps fish head soup, Love it

name: Little Eeden Sanur Bar and Restaurant
address: Jl. Matahari Terbit, Sanur Kaja, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali, Indonesia
review 1:
Superb! Very lucky to have visited this place on our first evening in Bali. Excellent food, large portion, beautifully presented, wonderfully helpful staff, and good prices.
Gotta also compliment the Bali White Wine, which I'm reliably informed is made here!
We're sailing the following morning, so came to reconoitre the location. Happy we did.
review 2: we had a lovely dinner at eeden! service and food was first class, and they even gave us complimentary crackers. everything came so quickly and was presented beautifully. could not recommend this restaurant enough!
review 3:
My husband was blown away by the flavour and tenderness of his 300g Beef Steak. The best he‚Äôs ever had in Bali! ‚úÖ
His chilled fresh coconut was delicious and my Margarita‚Ä¶.üò≥WOW!  My fish was delicious and the service was attentive without being overbearing. All in all a delightful meal! We will be going back for breakfast! üç∏‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚úÖ‚úÖ‚úÖ
I almost forgot‚Ä¶.The Apple Pie and icecream. Absolutely divine! üå∫
review 4:
Service was absolutely AMAZING! After a really hot ferry ride, walking up to this restaurant was seriously like stepping into Eden. The staff helped bring our luggage inside, and sat us right next to the AC. The cold towels were a god-send, and honestly I'd have suggested this place just for this reason. We pretty much used them to give ourselves sponge baths, and felt like real human beings again. Then, at the end of our meal, we had some issues receiving a call from our Gojek taxi driver. The staff was happy to help us, and called the driver from their own phones. Everyone working there seemed genuinely happy.

The food is good too, and also very well priced especially considering it's in a prime location.

HIGHLY recommend!!
review 5:
Was on our way to the sanur beach, passed by and decided to drop over.
No regrets!
Vibe was great in the restaurant.
The staff are friendly and there‚Äôs welcome drink with cold towel to refresh after the hot sun outside.
Foods and drinks are at affordable prices and the tastes are great and delicious.
In love with their tuna with purple sweet potato.
Coconut is very creative and cute with the craft.
There‚Äôs lot of varieties to choose from starters, main course, locals, dessert, fruits, drinks, coffee, juices, alcoholic drinks.
For sure will come over again very soon.
Do feel free to drop by for a try.

name: Infinity Coffee & Roastery
address: Pantai Matahari Terbit, Sanur Kaja, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1: Seriously good coffee! Amazing spot to stop before or after ferry to the islands. Beach views, great music, quality beans, creamy milk. Nothing not to love!   A buzzing local hang out area for students.
review 2:
Have you ever had a sip of coffee while watching the waves crash against the shore? Imagine yourself sitting on a beachside coffee shop drinking your refreshing cold brew, watching the sun rise over the water while listening to the soothing sounds of the ocean. Well, if you are looking for a place to relax and enjoy a cup of coffee, look no further.

In this oceanfront coffee shop, you will find all your favorite drinks, including specialty lattes, coffee, tea, and fresh juices. But what really sets this coffee shop apart from others is its stunning interior design that blends seamlessly with the natural elements around it, giving it a cozy and relaxing feel.

As you sip on your drink, you will notice the charming decor that includes natural wood pieces, vintage furniture and accessories, and of course, the breathtaking ocean views through the large windows. The coffee shop's unique and vintage style makes it an ideal destination for coffee lovers, beachgoers, and anyone looking for a peaceful and memorable experience.

So the next time you need a break from the hustle and bustle of daily life, or simply want to enjoy a cup of coffee while surrounded by nature's beauty, make sure to visit this beachside coffee shop. You won't regret it.
review 3: Best coffee in Bali so far made from scratch. Super nice and chill service. Definitely worth a visit while waiting for the ferry :)
review 4: great place to enjoy the beach, i went here at noon (around 11am) and theres shady spot so we wont got a heatstroke from the sun. the coffee tastes good tooüëç
review 5: Great place to relax and enjoying a cup of coffee while watching the sun goes down and enjoying the sound of the wave

name: Griya Shanti Suites
address: Jl. Matahari Terbit No.3, Sanur, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1:
I stayed at Griya for one month and would highly recommend it. The rooms are kept to what I‚Äôd describe as almost new standard and the cleanliness is something I‚Äôve not yet experienced in multiple previous visits to Bali.

Staff were friendly and helpful and the management team are also around daily and wanting to ensure guests are happy.

Location is brilliant and easy to access getting in and out to the other districts.

This place felt like my own mini home and I‚Äôll definitely return for short or long term stays.
review 2: Fantastic property, great rooms, very large and comfortable, clean and with all the necessary amenities.. great staff. The only downside is the poor breakfast, I would remove most of the breads and pastries that are tasteless, improve the quality of one bread, and make sure egg station is on for fresh eggs. I enjoyed the quietness while sunbathing and reading my book.
review 3:
Lovely spacious room with towels, robes and cooking amenities.

The staff were more than helpful, very polite and friendly.

We only stayed for one night but were very happy. The pool is currently under construction so once this is done it will be even better.

Great location to the harbour.
review 4: Beautiful accommodation! It was very comfortable during my stay. Also soft bedding! It's easy to sleep. I can enjoy my dinner while listening to an evening band at the bar located right in front. And breakfast is also free in there! Breakfast is delicious and plentiful. There is close to the port and Sanur Sea, making it a convenient location for boating. But since Grab is not available on this road, So you can walk or go to the main road and take a Grab taxi. There are many taxi drivers around the accommodation, but they are expensive.
review 5:
Room is very spacious and modern. The hotel is in a walking distance to the harbor if you want to visit Nusa Penida. Unfortunately, the pool was being renovated so we couldn‚Äôt swim.

The hotel is close to a big minimarket to get your everyday needs.

It‚Äôs hard to get online transportation cars/bikes here due to local conventional transportation vendors‚Äô policy ‚Äî you need to walk a little to the closest intersection.

name: Gria Umasari
address: Jl. Bypass Ngurah Rai No.150, Sanur, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1:
Very bad experience the hotel is on the sort of gihway and all the shop for averythink are to 30 minutes of distance and wi fi and AC didn t work

In the room there was umidity on the roof
review 2: We lived in this hotel for a week. Clean area, cozy atmosphere. They themselves offered to move to a better room for the same cost, they gave a hairdryer on request. Breakfast is not varied, but quite tasty. Cleaning every day. Nice pool with clean water. The location of the hotel is more suitable for tourists on transport, it is difficult to get to the beach area on foot, as there is a highway nearby. Very friendly owner and staff, thanks for the time spent.
review 3:
The room was nice clean. Good location close to the port .

They not clean your room very day not easy to find stuff. When I checked out I couldn‚Äôt see anyone until moving all my stuff from second floor and then I finally saw he when I was in front of the hotel because I have give them the motorbike‚Äôs key to them

Breakfast 5/10
review 4:
I recently had the pleasure of staying at the Gria Umasari in Sanur, Bali for a week-long vacation, and I must say it was an exceptional experience from start to finish.

First and foremost, the room provided was nothing short of wonderful. It was clean, neat, and spacious. The comfortable furnishings and tasteful decor added a touch of luxury, making me feel right at home throughout my stay. It was evident that the hotel takes great care in maintaining the rooms, as everything was in perfect order.

Gria Umasari is nestled in a peaceful area, away from the hustle and bustle of the city, providing a serene and calming atmosphere. Whether it was lounging by the pool or relaxing in the lush gardens, the entire setting exuded a sense of calmness that was perfect for a rejuvenating vacation.

One of the highlights of my stay was the exceptional staff at Gria Umasari. From the moment I arrived, I was greeted with warm smiles and genuine hospitality. The staff members were incredibly kind, friendly, and always willing to go above and beyond to ensure a pleasant stay. Their attentiveness and reliability were impressive, making me feel well taken care of throughout my time there.

Overall, my experience at Gria Umasari was nothing short of delightful, and I can confidently say that I will be returning whenever I visit Sanur, Bali in the future. The combination of the clean and spacious room, the calm and comfortable environment, and the genuinely kind and reliable staff made my vacation truly memorable.

If you're seeking a peaceful and charming getaway in Bali, I highly recommend Gria Umasari. Whether you're traveling solo or with loved ones, the hotel's inviting ambiance and top-notch service will surely leave you with a lasting impression and a desire to return.
review 5: Stay here for 1 night before Bali marathon because the place is near of the shuttle pin point. Staffs are friendly, the rooms are clean, above expectation for value of money. good job üëå

name: Bandar Tuna Sanur (BTS)
address: Jl. Bypass Ngurah Rai No.158A, Sanur Kaja, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1: Food is not delicious. I can not eat anything and my friends have to eat all. Fish is not fresh. The soup is like cup noodles soup. No one but us in the restaurant. Not recommended if you visit Bali.
review 2:
the food was good. i like that.
the place was cozy and not crowded so really can enjoy around.
i order nasi campur bandar tuna, and mix the sweet sambal with a bit spicy sambal for me. and the taste for the sambal perfectly good for me.
review 3:
Literally one of the best tuna steaks I've ever had! And sate tuna is amazing as well! Must try! Prices are really comfortable, even tho they've got 11% extra tax, but it's still pretty fine. The steak (dada tuna bakar) was large and delicious, you'll love the local seasonings. And it wasn't too spicy as I requested.

But the only one small concern‚Ä¶ they don't remove the fish scales‚Ä¶ so it looks like a steak but when you're taking a bite, all the scales are going right into your mouth. It's not a big problem, but it's weird. So I believe, it'd be quite better if you descale the fish before cooking üòÖ
review 4: Loved my early dinner at BTS! The tuna skewers - marinated perfection - and incredibly fresh tuna tataki stole the show. The aglio e olio with tuna (get it with chili!) was bursting with flavor. While other dishes were good, the tuna reigned supreme. Great atmosphere, reasonable prices, and easy parking. Highly recommend!
review 5: This was my first time here, and everything went well. The food was good, especially the three types of sambal. The fish was also okay. The service was friendly during our dining time. However, there might need to be more attention to the table, as there is dust due to its proximity to the busy street.

name: Asian Pantry

review 1: Had an ice latte (strong coffee) and bacon bagel. The air conditioning is great in here perfect place to cool off between the ferry and the road to grab your taxi home . Highly recommend
review 2: This place has the best coffee at Sanur Harbour which is always needed when you have a early boat. The new banana cake was so good we had to order a 2nd. Wifi is great so could get some work done whilst waiting for boat departure.

review 4:
we stopped after arriving from Nusa Penida, the waiters were very rude, almost disturbed, we asked them to eat outside and they made absurd faces!!!
we took two spring rolls and two cokes, we had to wait more than 45 minutes, after various requests these famous spring rolls arrived, horrible to say the least, you couldn't eat them in any way... it made you vomit ü§Æ
review 5: Small place with a really good Pad Thai and a good Teriyaki Chicken. Prices are reasonable and the staff is friendly. I don't give 5 stars only because there was a bad smell inside, usually from a wet mop that never dries.

Friendly service and fast serving of his food.
review 5: Ordered the set menu. Got the fried fish and fish soup. Taste is great but not that awesome. name: Merpati Cafe

review 5: Really great and calm place for dine in. Great variety of food items and they are worth the price. The staff is really friendly. The washrooms are clean and the kitchen looks hygienic.

name: Awake coffee & eatery

The staff at the bar was very nice!
review 3:
A great little place to have a coffee and a snack while you are waiting for your boat!
They have great coffee drinks and smoothies, as well as other drinks.
Sandwiches and pastries are available and are very good and reasonably priced.
They have vegetarian options, and they can make your coffee drinks with oat or almond milk, too.
They take cash only, so be prepared
review 4: Great coffee, music and energy from the staff. We were waiting for the ferry there and was a pleasure.
review 5:
The amenities don't match the price of the menu.
Heavily overpriced menu items and they don't accept card, don't have fans or AC and just straight up ghetto design.

Would prefer to enjoy my coffee without second hand smoke clouds.

name: WARUNG LAISAN SANUR
address: Ruko MGA kav 3 jl Pantai Matahari Terbit, Sanur Kaja, Denpasar Selatan, Denpasar City, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1: We found this Warung on Google maps while looking for a place for lunch. Saw good reviews on Google about their seafood items. We wanted to get a medium or large fish grill, but they only had jumbo fish. The price on the menu was 175k, but they said it's 190k. We also ordered a few other items, including their famous clams for 55k per kg. In my opinion, the food was too expensive but the taste wasn't exceptional but decent. They were selling tea, samosa, and spring rolls for 30k each. The grill fish came out quite burnt. The skin was too thick to eat. Taste was ok. Clams were nice, but the sauce they used was overpowering. Overall, it was ok but not worth the hype, especially considering the price. I do understand that the restaurant is located close to a touristy area but still felt like we were overcharged massively.
review 2: Hidden gem in Sanur! The restaurant doesn't look like much from the outside but I had one of the best grilled clams and squid here during my entire Bali trip. The sauce on the kerang is to die for and the cumi had an amazing char-grill taste. I would definitely recommend folks to give it a try!
review 3: The best shrimp I have ever had! I had to order a second plate it was so good.  I grew up on the beach and am very familiar with high-quality seafood, and that's exactly what this is. Do not miss this unassuming restaurant, It will blow you away.
review 4: The fish is so good! Fried rice is also delicious!
review 5: Best taste of seafood. I love the grilled clams, plecing and sambal matah. The fish is fresh from the fisherman in Sanur. The price is cheap because all including rice & plecing .The owner is friendly. Very recomended for the seafood lover.

name: Cafe Juna
address: 87H6+R9P, Sanur Kaja, Denpasar Selatan, Denpasar City, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1:
Small cozy cafe in Sanur. You could take a break and enjoying the sea view from here.

I really enjoyed the sea breeze with croissant and hot latte. The croissant was nice but the latte is okay, maybe because I prefer a stronger coffee.

Other than that, the staff are really friendly and helpful. It was nice to visit this cafe üòÅ
review 2:
We had coffee of various types and other drinks here today before our fast boat whisked us away to an island off Bali called Nusa Penida.
Excellent coffee of all sorts, cold drinks and cakes at ok prices.
Friendly staff as well.
Highly recommend if near this little but amazing coffee rest stop.
review 3: What more can you ask for? Chill lounge music, good coffee and fresh pastries with an ocean view off the Balinese coast. Aces!
review 4: We had coffee whuch quite good. Simple pastries taste ok. Hood place to meet your freind
review 5: Expensive sandwich and coffee shop in harbour. Food was average. Try shops outside of harbour for better deal

name: Pantai Dermaga
address: 87M6+F9, Kesiman, East Denpasar, Denpasar City, Bali 80237, Indonesia

name: The Lavana Townhouse Sanur

name: BEN'S JOGLO
address: Jl. Hangtuah III No.18, Sanur, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80227, Indonesia
review 1: We had an iced late and iced cappuccino. Their coffee is so good.
review 2: Lovely place to have great coffee and tasty, refreshing drinks. Great service and friendly hosts. Highly recommend.
review 3: Soft opening: espresso coffee and cold beer already available. There is a direct walking path to the harbour and this place allows grab, gocar and other taxi to enter.
review 4: Really good and cozy place will open soon
